Rayshader base tutorial and bonus

Rayshader可以生成美观的三维地形图.David Solito写的一篇博文A Rayshader base tutorial + Bonus : Hawaii具有很好的参考意义，用于生成实际的三维地形也简单明了.

Load library

library(rayshader)
library(raster)
library(png)
library(rgl)
knitr::knit_hooks$set(webgl = hook_webgl)

下载地形数据

Opentopography网站提供了地形数据下载界面。浏览地图至需要下载地形数据的区域，采用“Select a region”工具选取地图范围。之后选择地形数据库，一般使用GMRT数据。选择数据输出格式为GeoTiff，分辨率为最大Max，另外要选择“Generate additional color-relief and colored hillshades”，生成png图片用于三维地形表面的纹理。

三维地形可视化

Read and preprocess data.

# read raster file
elevation <- "data/output_gmrt.tif"
elevation.raster <- raster::raster(elevation)

# extract and convert to matrix
elevation.matrix <- matrix(extract(elevation.raster, 
                                   extent(elevation.raster), buffer = 100), 
                           nrow=ncol(elevation.raster), ncol=nrow(elevation.raster))

# set zscale
my.z <- 30

# get texture
elevation.texture.map <- readPNG("data/viz.gmrt.crhs.white.png")

Test map.

elevation.matrix  %>% 
  sphere_shade(sunangle = 35, texture = "imhof1", zscale = my.z) %>%
  plot_map()
